To use a conditional statement, combine it with an existing OpenROAD Call Statement:
```
if (sex = 'M') then 
    call rungraph(graph = 'male_customers', device = 'screen');
else
    call rungraph(graph = 'female_customers', device = 'screen');
endif;
```

To execute an OpenROAD application in batch mode:
```
commit;
call runimage(filename = 'runimage', startcomponent = 'framename', batchmode = 'on');
```
This will run the application without displaying any interactive frames.

To call the custom dialog box:
```
commit;
call dialog('custom-dialog', param1, param2);
```
This will display the custom-built dialog box with the specified parameters.

To call a stored procedure:
```
commit;
call sp_name(param1, param2);
```
This will execute the stored procedure 'sp_name' with the specified parameters.

To call a program:
```
commit;
call program('program-name', param1, param2);
```
This will execute the program 'program-name' with the specified parameters.

To call the stored procedure using Actian 4GL OpenROAD Call Statement:
```
commit;
call sp_insert_customer(100, 'John Doe');
```
This will execute the stored procedure with the specified parameters.

To handle exceptions when calling a program:
```
commit;
begin
   call program('program_name', param1, param2);
exception
   WHEN OTHERS THEN
      print "Error occurred: " && sqlerrm;
end;
```
This code block will call the program and handle any exceptions that occur.
